# Mandatory agent compliance

**Binding:** Every rule in `.cursor/rules/` applies to this repository. Do not skip, summarize away, or override them with generic best practices. When in doubt, read the full rule file.

## Always in context (`alwaysApply: true`)

These are injected every session — follow them on **every** task (questions, reviews, fixes, features, commits, PRs):

| Rule | Non‑negotiable |
|------|----------------|
| `agents-mandatory.mdc` | This file — compliance gate |
| `delivery-workflow.mdc` | Plan → implement → test → review → CI |
| `review-commit.mdc` | Self-review, commit/PR policy, merge blockers |
| `architecture-clean.mdc` | Layer boundaries, screen models, navigation |
| `kmp-core.mdc` | Stack, AppNavigator, Koin, Compose, coroutines |
| `i18n-multilingual.mdc` | 8 locales, no hardcoded UI copy |
| `official-docs-urls.mdc` | Confirm APIs against indexed docs |
| `ui-ux-compose.mdc` | Journey design system, UX states, testTags |
| `qa-testing.mdc` | Unit/instrumented tests, Firebase YAML |

## Scoped rules — read before editing matching paths

If your task touches these paths, **read the rule file first** (use the Read tool):

| Paths | Rule file |
|-------|-----------|
| `data/**` (non-supabase) | `backend-data.mdc` |
| `supabase/**`, `data/supabase/**` | `supabase-backend.mdc` |
| `.github/**`, `firebase*.yaml`, `gradle/app-version.properties` | `ci-cd.mdc` |
| `iosMain/**`, `iosApp/**` | `ios-platform.mdc` |

## Task-start checklist (agents)

1. **Classify task** — implementation, review, test-only, docs, release, question.
2. **Plan** per `delivery-workflow.mdc` — layers, i18n, tests, QA YAML.
3. **Read scoped rules** from the table above if paths will change.
4. **Implement** using `architecture-clean`, `kmp-core`, `ui-ux-compose`, `i18n-multilingual`.
5. **Test** per `qa-testing.mdc` — run Gradle tasks before claiming done.
6. **Self-review** per `review-commit.mdc` before PR/commit.
7. **CI/release** per `ci-cd.mdc` when pushing or releasing.

## Task-end checklist (before "done")

- [ ] Layer boundaries respected (no UI in domain/data; no `*Impl` in composables)
- [ ] All new strings in **8** locale `strings.xml` files
- [ ] Journey components / semantic colors (no raw Material forms or one-off hex)
- [ ] Tests added or updated; `:composeApp:testDebugUnitTest` run
- [ ] `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` updated if user-facing flows changed
- [ ] No secrets committed; commit only if user explicitly asked

## Reviews & commits

- **Code review:** Use `review-commit.mdc` priority table (P0 security → P4 style).
- **Commits:** Only when user asks; message explains **why**; never skip hooks.
- **PRs:** Test plan required; wait for CI green before merge.

